data.title: Great tacos but safety is very bad
data.text: I used to visit this place a lot because their tacos tastes very authentic but there was an incident that happened when I was parked in their lot, a car hit the back of my car. I didn't worry much because I know they have a lot of surveillance camera. So I reported it in the Police Department so they can pull out the video and find information but unfortunately, the owner was very uncooperative and the Officer told me that the camera was probably just for decoration. So after that, I don't go there anymore. I don't feel as much safe as before. I'm pretty sure I can find other authentic Mexican in the area. Try Sabor next time. Also, just FYI, this restaurant only accepts cash. The taste is good but not worth it when your car will get hit in their parking lot.

data.title: Great after all these years!
data.text: We used to live in the area and miss the food at Sper taco. Every time we come to the area we stop in for the best burrito we have ever had. Even after 30 years the food is still worth the trip!

data.title: Pretty good
data.text: Super Taco was the place to get a quick bite for years but has recently changed. The recipes seem to have been altered and the burritos seemed dry. I used to make this a must have on my Oxnard visits but now I'll pass.

data.title: Not Clean
data.text: Not sure of the standards of some of the other people which posted reviews. The place needs to be inspected for proper cleaning and food temperatures.

data.title: A Tradition To Eat At Super Taco
data.text:
As a kid, when my family would enjoy a weekend joyride through the town, or if I were departing from the Oxnard Train Depot for a trip somewhere - I'd always want to stop in at Super Taco for a huge tasty Burrito. 
If anyone would ask, it's nothing special on the outside. Just a quaint little place we found many years ago, and the same family has owned it for many years. You order at the window outside, and there's limited seating indoors. If you've ever felt sentimental about a 'whole-in-the-wall' taco stand...this is your place to come!

data.title: Yummm!!
data.text: I love this place... I grew up calling it fifth street... and its not even on fifth street... omg... the absolute BEST carne asada and carnitas tacos in the world... everything is phenomenal. .. and the chili relleno burritos are the super bomb digity!!

data.title: burritos are huge!
data.text: this place has been here forever.  it is open late.  they make ur food right in front of you.  prices are reasonable.  horchata is good. i have been coming here since i was teenager, and for good reason

data.title: Great Chili Relleno Burro
data.text: You order at the window and they have a area with small booths (dirty) on the side where you can eat.  They have tacos and burritos of all types.  I had the chili relleno burrito and it was as good as any I have had.  Inexpensive.  They have good soft drink selections.  Good place to grab an inexpensive burrito.

data.title: NACHOS
data.text: we've been going to super taco for years and they have amazing nachos! right in downtown oxnard. the staff has always been nice and their verde sauce is awesome. It's too bad it's right next door to TDM, but if you want a good nacho i love their's over most in the area.

data.title: Super Taco Cravings!
data.text:
My first day on the job as a Navy Petty Officer stationed at Point Mugu, two of my peers rushed me out to Super Taco (Which we affectionately refer to as "5th street burrito") for lunch. "Order quick!" I was told ... and so I did. We rushed back to the base, rushed back to our office, and sat down for the last 7 minutes of our lunch break and ate our burritos. DELICIOUSLY PERFECT!! One of my peers, a male, always orders the carne asada. My other peer and myself order the marinated beef burrito. Black beans, rice (YES!), sour cream, cheese, tomatoes, hot sauce, and cilantro. Perfection in a burrito shell. Heavenly lunch, paired with a large root beer!

I've been craving Super Tacos perfect burritos since I left California 7 years ago, and hopefully I will finally get to have another one this fall. Otherwise, I am going to have to seriously consider having one sent to me by Fed Ex so that I can enjoy the perfection once again!

data.title: best on the planet
data.text: Super Taco has the best mexican food I've ever tasted bar none.  Ive gone to other mexican restaurants in the area (El taco de Mexico, tacos la placita, el tapatio, baja fresh... etc) nothing compares to Super Taco.  I recommend the Asada Burrito with Chile Relleno let me just tell its the BOMB!!! Give it a try its located on the corner of 5th street in Oxnard near the amtrak station.
